quran[339]{c,v,t}:
  25,21,"And the ones who do not hope for a meeting with Us have said, \"Had there been (the) Angels sent down upon us, or (had it been for us to) see our Lord!\" Indeed they have already waxed proud within themselves and have rebelled a great rebellion"
  25,22,"The Day that they see the Angels, no good tidings (will be) for the criminals upon that Day, and they will say, \"An utter restriction!\" (Literally: a restriction restricted; i.e., good news is, utterly restricted from the criminals)"
  25,23,"And We will go forward to whatever deed they have done and so make it a strewn motes. (i.e., dust)"
  25,24,"The companions (i.e., inhabitants) of the Garden upon that Day, more charitable (i.e., better) will be their repository, (i.e., dwelling habitation) and fairer their halting-place"
  25,25,"And the Day that the heaven is cloven with the mist and the Angels are sent down, a (successive) sending down"
  25,26,"The Kingdom, upon that Day, the true (Kingdom), will belong to The All-Merciful, and it will ever be a Day difficult for the disbelievers"
  25,27,"And the Day that the unjust (person) will bite at both his hands, (and) say, \"Oh, would that I had taken to myself a way along with the Messenger"
  25,28,"Oh, woe to me! Would that I had not taken so-and-so to myself for a (close) fellow"
  25,29,"Indeed he readily made me err away from the Remembrance after it had come to me.\" And Ash-Shaytan (i.e., dwelling habitation) has been constantly abandoning man"
  25,30,"And the Messenger has said, \"O Lord! Surely my people have taken to themselves this Qur'an as a thing to be forsaken"
  25,31,And thus We have made to every Prophet an enemy among the criminals; and your Lord suffices as a Guide and an Ever-Vindicator
  25,32,"And the ones who have disbelieved have said, \"If only the Qur'an had been sent down upon him as one complete whole.\" Thus, that We may make firm your heart-sight thereby, and We have recited it in a (distinct) recitation"
  25,33,"And they do not come up to you with any similitude, except that We come to you with the Truth and a fairer explanation"
  25,34,"The ones who will be mustered to Hell upon their faces, those will be in an eviler place and will have (erred) further from the way"
  25,35,"And indeed We already brought Musa (Moses) the Book, and We made with him his brother Harun (Aaron) as minister"
  25,36,"So We said, \"Go you (both) to the people who have cried lies to Our signs.\" Then We destroyed them an utter destruction"
  25,37,"And the people of Nuh, (Noah) as soon as they cried lies to the Messengers, We drowned them, and We made them to be a sign to mankind; and We have readied for the unjust a painful torment"
  25,38,"And Aad, and Thamud, and the companions (i.e., inhabitants) of Ar-Rass, and between them (Literally: that) many generations"
  25,39,"And for each We struck similitudes, and each We annihilated utterly (Literally: annihilated annihilation)"
  25,40,"And indeed they already came up to the town which was rained on by a woeful rain. Have they then not seen it? No indeed, (but) they did not hope for an uprising (i.e., resurrection)"
  25,41,"And when they see you, they decidedly take you to themselves for nothing except in mockery, \"Is this he whom Allah has sent forth as a Messenger"
  25,42,"Decidedly he had almost made us, indeed, to err away from our gods, had we not (suffered ourselves) to endure patiently with them.\" And eventually they will know, while they see the tornment, who has erred further from the way"
  25,43,Have you seen him who has taken to himself his prejudice to be his god? Will you then be a constant trustee over him
  25,44,"Or even do you reckon that most of them hear or consider? Decidedly they are (nothing) except as the cattle. (Ancam inclues cattle, camels, sheep and goats) No indeed, they have erred further from the way"
  25,45,"Have you not regarded your Lord, how He has extended the shade? And if He had so decided, He would indeed have made it still. Thereafter We made the sun a constant indicator of it"
  25,46,"Thereafter We grasped it to Us, an easy (Or: gradual) grasping"
  25,47,And He is the One Who has made the night for you (to be) a garment and sleep for repose and has made day-time for rising
  25,48,"And He is the One Who has sent the winds, bearing good tidings before (Literally: between the two hands of His mercy) His mercy; and We have sent down from the heaven water most pure"
  25,49,"That We may give life to a deceased country, and we make to drink of it, of whatever We created, many cattle and human beings"
  25,50,And indeed We have already propounded it among them so that they may constantly remember; yet most mankind refuse (anything) except constant disbelief
  25,51,And if We had so decided We would indeed have sent forth in every town a constant warner
  25,52,"So do not obey the disbelievers, and strive with them thereby with a constantly great striving"
  25,53,"And He is the One Who has merged the two seas, this one sweet, grateful (to taste), and this salt, bitter (to the tongue); and He has made between them an isthmus, and an utter- obstruction. (Literally: obstruction obstructed)"
  25,54,And He is The One Who created of water a mortal; so He has made him related by blood and marriage; and your Lord has been Ever-Determiner
  25,55,"And they worship, apart from Allah, what neither profits them nor harms them; and the disbeliever has been a backer against his Lord"
  25,56,And in no way have We sent you except (as) a bearer of good tidings and a constant warner
  25,57,"Say, \"In no way do I ask of you (any) reward for it except for him who decides to take for (himself) a way to his Lord"
  25,58,"(And put your trust in the Living Allah) Who does not die, and extol with His praise. And He suffices as The Ever-Cognizant of His bondmen's guilty deeds"
  25,59,"(He is the one) who created the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them, in six days; thereafter He leveled Himself upon the Throne. (How He did so is beyond human understanding) (He is) The All-Merciful, so ask any cognizant of Him"
  25,60,"And when it is said to them, \"Prostrate yourselves to The All-Merciful, \" they have said, \"And what is The All-Merciful? Shall we prostrate ourselves to what you command us?\" And it has increased them in repulsion. * A prostraion is to be peformed after reading this"
  25,61,"Supremely Blessed is He Who has made in the heaven constellations, and He has made therein a luminary and an enlightening moon"
  25,62,"And He is the One Who has made the night and day-time a succession for whomever is willing to constantly remember (Or: for whomever He wills to be mindful; or: whomever He wills) or whomever is willing to give constant thanks"
  25,63,"And the bondmen of The All-Merciful are the ones who walk on the earth gently, and when the ignorant address them, they say, \"Peace"
  25,64,"And the ones who spend the night, (constantly) prostrating and upright to their lord"
  25,65,"And the ones who say, \"Our Lord, turn about (i.e., turn away) from us the torment of Hell; surely its torment is (really) a (grievous) penalty"
  25,66,Surely odious it is as a repository and a stationing
  25,67,"And the ones who, when they expend, are neither extravagant nor grudging; and between that is an upright (mean)"
  25,68,"And the ones who do not invoke another god (along) with Allah, nor kill the self that Allah has prohibited except with the truth nor commit adultery; (i.e., illegal sexual intercourse) and whoever performs that will meet the penalty for vice"
  25,69,"Doubled will be the torment for him on the Day of the Resurrection, and he will eternally (abide) therein degraded"
  25,70,"Except him who repents, and believes, and does righteous deed (s). So those, Allah will turn (Or: substitue fair deeds in place of odious ones) their odious (deeds) into fair (deeds); and Allah has been Ever-Forgiving, Ever-Merciful"
  25,71,"And whoever repents and does righteousness, then surely he repents to Allah a (true) repenting"
  25,72,"And who do not testify to false witness (i.e., illegal sexual intercourse) and, when they pass by idle talk, pass by honorably"
  25,73,"And who, when they are reminded of the signs of their Lord, do not collapse there deaf and totally blind (Literally: all- blind)"
  25,74,"And who say, \"Our Lord, bestow upon us from our spouses and offsprings comfort of the eyes, (Literally: the coolness (when)the eyes settle down) and make us an imam (Leader) of the pious"
  25,75,"Those will be recompensed with the compartment (s) for that they (endured) patiently, and they shall be granted therein a greeting and \"Peace"
  25,76,Eternally (abiding) therein; fair it is as a repository and a stationing
  25,77,"Say, (To the disbelievers)\" In no way would my Lord care for you were it not for your invocation. Yet you have cried lies, so it (Punishment) will eventually be an imposition"
  26,1,"Ta, Sin, Mim. (These are the names of letters of Arabic alphabet, and only Allah knows their meaning here)"
  26,2,"Those (Literally: that). are the ayat (Verses, signs) of the evident Book"
  26,3,You would possibly consume yourself that they are not believers
  26,4,"In case We (so) decide, We will be sending down on them from the heaven a sign so their necks linger subdued to it"
  26,5,And in no way does a recent Remembrance come up to them from The All-Merciful except they are veering away from it
  26,6,Then they have readily cried lies; so the tidings will soon come up to them of what they used to mock at
  26,7,"And have they not regarded the earth, how many therein We have caused to grow of every honorable pair"
  26,8,Surely in that is indeed a sign; and in no way were most of them believers
  26,9,"And surely your Lord, He is indeed The Ever Mighty, The Ever-Merciful"
  26,10,"And as your Lord called out to Musa, (Moses) (saying), \"Come up to the unjust people"
  26,11,The people of Firaawn. (Pharaoh) Will they not be pious
  26,12,"He said, \"Lord! Surely I fear they will cry me lies"
  26,13,"And my breast will be straitened, and my tongue will not be free. (i.e., it will not express well; literally, will not go off freely) So send to Harun. (Aaron)"
  26,14,And they have a guilty deed against me; so I fear they will kill me
  26,15,"Said He, \"Not at all, so go (both of you) with Our signs; surely We will be with you, listening"
  26,16,"So come up to Firaawn, then say (to him), \"We (both) are the Messenger of The Lord of the worlds"
  26,17,"(Saying) Send forth with us the Seeds (Or: sons) of .\" Israel"
  26,18,"Said he, \"Did we not rear you among us as a newborn, and did you not linger among us years of your age"
  26,19,And you performed the performance you performed and you were one of the disbelievers
  26,20,"He (Musa) (Moses) said, \"lo, I performed it and I was of the erring"
  26,21,So I fled from you as soon as I feared you. Then my Lord bestowed upon me judgment and He made me one of the Emissaries
  26,22,"And is that a favor you oblige me with, that you have taken the Seeds (Or: sons) of Israel) as slaves"
  26,23,"Firaawn (Pharaoh) said, \"And what is The Lord of the worlds"
  26,24,"He said, \"The Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them (both), in case you have certitude"
  26,25,"He said to the ones around him, \"Do you not listen"
  26,26,"He said, \"Your Lord and The Lord of your earliest fathers"
  26,27,"He said, \"Surely your Messenger who has been sent to you is indeed a madman"
  26,28,"He said, \"The Lord of the east and the west and whatever is between them (both), in case you (can) consider"
  26,29,"He said, \"Indeed in case you take to yourself a god other than me, indeed I will definitely make you one of the imprisoned"
  26,30,"He said, \"Even if I come to you with (some) thing evident"
  26,31,"He said, \"Come up with it then, in case you are of the sincere ones"
  26,32,"So he cast his staff, then, only then was it a (demonstrably) evident serpent"
  26,33,"And he drew out his hand, then, only then was it white to the onlookers"
  26,34,"He (Firaawn) said to the chiefs around him, \"Surely this is indeed a knowledgeable sorcerer"
  26,35,Who would like to drive you out of your land by his sorcery; so what do you command
  26,36,"They said, \"Put him off, (him) and his brother, and send forth into the cities musterers"
  26,37,"Who will come up to you with every crafty, knowledgeable sorcerer"
  26,38,So the sorcerers were gathered (together) for the fixed time on a known day. (A day of festival)
  26,39,"And it was said to the citizens, \"Will you be gathered (together)"
  26,40,"That possibly we would closely follow the sorcerers, in case they are the ones who are the overcomers"
  26,41,"Then, when the sorcerers came, they said to Firaawn, (Pharaoh) \"will we surely have a reward indeed, in case we are the ones who are the overcomers"
  26,42,"He said, \"Yes, and lo indeed, surely you will be indeed among the near-stationed"
  26,43,"Musa (Moses) said to them, \"Cast you down whatever you will be casting"
  26,44,"So they cast down their ropes and their staffs and said, \"By the might of Firaawn, we, surely we, will indeed be the overcomers"
  26,45,"Then Musa cast down his staff, then, only then did it gulp whatever falshood they (showed)"
  26,46,"So the sorcerers were cast down, prostrating themselves"
  26,47,"They said, \"We believe in The Lord of the worlds"
  26,48,"The Lord of Musa and Harun.\" (Aaron)"
  26,49,"He (Firaawn) said, \"You have believed him before I give you permission. Surely he is indeed your great (master) who taught you sorcery. Yet indeed you will eventually know! Indeed I will definitely cut off (The form of the verb implies something done repeatedly, or to a high degree or great extent. (cf. surat yusuf 3 1) your hands and legs alternately, and indeed I will definitely crucify you all together"
  26,50,"They said, \"It is no trouble; surely to our Lord we are turning back. (Literally: turning over)"
  26,51,"Surely we long for (the fact) that our Lord should forgive us our sins, for that we are the first of the believers"
  26,52,"And We revealed to Musa, (saying), \"Set forth with My bondmen by night. Surely you will be closely followed"
  26,53,Then Firaawn sent among the cities musterers
  26,54,Surely these are indeed a gang of a few (persons)
  26,55,And surely they are indeed enraging us
  26,56,And surely we are indeed all wary
  26,57,"So We drove them out of gardens, and springs"
  26,58,"And hoardings, and an honorable station"
  26,59,"Thus, We gave them as an inheritance to the Seeds (Or: sons) of Israel"
  26,60,"So they (Firaawn) (Pharaoh) and his hosts) followed them up at sunshine. (Or: going East)"
  26,61,"Then, as soon as the two gatherings sighted each other, the companions of Musa (Moses) said, \"Surely we are indeed overtaken"
  26,62,"He said, \"Not at all. Surely my Lord is with me; He will soon guide me"
  26,63,"Then We revealed to Musa, (saying), \"Strike with your staff the sea.\" So it split, and each (separate) part was as a tremendous towering mountain"
  26,64,And We drew forward the others there
  26,65,And We delivered Musa and the ones with him all together
  26,66,Thereafter We drowned the others
  26,67,"Surely in that is indeed a sign, and in no way were most of them believers"
  26,68,"And surely your Lord, He is indeed The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Merciful"
  26,69,"And recite to them the tiding ofIbrahim, (Abraham)"
  26,70,"As he said to his father and his people, \"What do you worship"
  26,71,"They said, \"We worship idols, so we linger on consecrating (ourselves) to them"
  26,72,"He said, \"Do they hear you as you invoke (them)"
  26,73,Or do they profit you or harm (you)
  26,74,"They said, \"No indeed, (but) we found our fathers thus performing"
  26,75,"He said, \"Have you then seen what you have been worshiping"
  26,76,You and your fathers of old
  26,77,"Yet, surely they are an enemy to me, except The Lord of the worlds"
  26,78,"Who created me. And so He, Ever He, guides me"
  26,79,"And (it is He) Who, Ever He, feeds me and He gives me to drink"
  26,80,"And when I am sick, then He, Ever He, cures me"
  26,81,And (it is He) Who makes me to die; thereafter He gives me life
  26,82,"And Whom I long (that) He will forgive me my offense (s) on the Day of Doom. (Or: Judgment)"
  26,83,"My Lord! Bestow upon me judgment, and join me with the righteous"
  26,84,And make for me a tongue of sincerity (Truthfulness) in the later (generations)
  26,85,And make me among the heirs of the Garden of Bliss
  26,86,And forgive my father; surely he is one of the erring
  26,87,And do not disgrace me the Day when they are made to rise (again)
  26,88,The Day when neither money nor sons will profit (anyone)
  26,89,Except for him who comes up to Allah with a sound heart
  26,90,And the Garden will be drawn forward for the pious
  26,91,And Hell Fire will be brought forth for the misguided
  26,92,"And it will be said to them, \"Where is that which you used to worship"
  26,93,Apart from Allah? Do they vindicate you or vindicate themselves
  26,94,"Then they will be pitched (headlong) into it, they and the misguided"
  26,95,"And the hosts ofIblis, all together"
  26,96,"They will say, (as) they stood therein, adversaries with each other"
  26,97,"By Allah, decidedly we were indeed in evident error"
  26,98,As we made you equal with The Lord of the worlds
  26,99,And in no way did anybody lead us into error except the criminals
  26,100,So (now) in no way do we have any intercessors
  26,101,Nor any intimate friend
  26,102,"So, if we had (a chance) to recur, (i.e., to live again) then we should be among the believers"
  26,103,Surely in that is indeed a sign; and in no way were most of them believers
  26,104,"And surely your Lord, He is indeed The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Merciful"
  26,105,The people of Nuh (Noah) cried lies to the Emissaries
  26,106,"As their brother Nuh said to them, \"Will you not be pious"
  26,107,Surely I am for you a trustworthy Messenger
  26,108,"So be pious to Allah, and obey me"
  26,109,And in no way do I ask of you any reward for (this); decidedly my reward (falls) upon no one except The Lord of the worlds
  26,110,"So be pious to Allah, and obey me"
  26,111,"They said, \"should we believe you, and the most decrepit closely follow you"
  26,112,"He said, \"What knowledge have I of whatever they were doing"
  26,113,"Decidedly their reckoning (falls) upon no one except my Lord, if you are aware"
  26,114,And in no way would I drive away the believers
  26,115,Decidedly I am nothing except an evident warner
  26,116,"They said, \"Indeed, decidedly in case you do not refrain, O Nuh, (Noah) indeed you will definitely be one of the stoned"
  26,117,"He said, \"Lord! Surely my people have cried me lies"
  26,118,"So arbitrate between me and them a (conclusive) arbitration, and deliver me safely and the ones who are with me of the believers"
  26,119,"So We delivered him, and the ones with him, in the laden ship"
  26,120,Thereafter We drowned afterwords the remaining ones
  26,121,Surely in that is indeed a sign; and in no way were most of them believers
  26,122,"And surely your Lord, He is indeed The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Merciful"
  26,123,Aad cried lies to the Emissaries
  26,124,"As their brother H?d said to them, \"Will you not be pious"
  26,125,Surely I am for you a trustworthy Messenger
  26,126,"So be pious to Allah, and obey me"
  26,127,And in no way do I ask of you any reward for (this); decidedly my reward (falls) upon no one except The Lord of the worlds
  26,128,"Do you build on every prominence a sign, sporting? (i.e., huge prominence inspiring fear)"
  26,129,"And do you take to yourselves castles (Or: huge buildings and tombs) that possibly you may abide eternally"
  26,130,"And when you assault, you assault as potentates"
  26,131,"So be pious to Allah, and obey me"
  26,132,And be pious to Him Who has supplied you with whatever you know
  26,133,"He has supplied you with cattle (Ancam includes cattle, camels, sheep, and goats) and sons"
  26,134,And gardens and springs
  26,135,Surely I fear for you the torment of a tremendous Day
  26,136,"They said, \"It is equal to us, whether you admonish or you are not one of the admonishers"
  26,137,Decidedly this is nothing except the character of the earliest (people)
  26,138,And in no way will we be tormented
  26,139,"So they cried him lies, then We caused them to perish. Surely in that is indeed a sign; and in no way were most of them believers"
  26,140,"And surely your Lord, He is indeed The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Merciful"
  26,141,Thamud cried lies to the Emissaries
  26,142,"As their brother Salih said to them, \"Will you not be pious"
  26,143,Surely I am for you a trustworthy Messenger
  26,144,"So be pious to Allah, and obey me"
  26,145,And in no way do I ask of you any reward for (this); decidedly my reward (falls) upon no one except The Lord of the worlds
  26,146,Will you be left secure in what you have here now
  26,147,In gardens and springs
  26,148,"And plantations, and palm trees with spathes slender (and) digestible? (Or: heavy spthes)"
  26,149,And you (skillfully) hew houses out of the mountains
  26,150,"So be pious to Allah, and obey me"
  26,151,And do not obey the command of the extravagant
  26,152,"Who corrupt in the earth, and do not act righteously"
  26,153,"They said, \"Surely you are only one of the utterly bewitched"
  26,154,"In no way are you (anything) except a mortal, like us. Then come up with a sign, in case you are one of the sincere"
  26,155,"He said, \"This is a she-camel. To her is a (time of) drinking and to you (another time of) drinking, on a known day"
  26,156,And do not touch her with an odious (treatment) so that there takes you (away) the torment of a Tremendous Day
  26,157,"Yet they hamstrung her, (and) so they became remorseful"
  26,158,"Then the torment took them (away). Surely in that is indeed a sign, and in no way were most of them believers"
  26,159,"And surely your Lord, He is indeed The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Merciful"
  26,160,The people of Lut (Lot) cried lies to the Emissaries
  26,161,"As their brother L?t said to them, \"Will you not be pious"
  26,162,Surely I am for you a trustworthy Messenger
  26,163,"So be pious to Allah, and obey me"
  26,164,And in no way do I ask of you any reward for (this); decidedly my reward (falls) upon no one except The Lord of the worlds
  26,165,Do you come up to (stout) males of the worlds
  26,166,"And leave behind what your Lord created for you as spouses? No indeed, (but) you are an aggressive people"
  26,167,"They said, \"Indeed in case you do not refrain, O L?t, indeed you will definitely be of the driven out"
  26,168,"He said, \"Surely I am of the disfavorers of your doing. (i.e., idisapprove of what you are doing)"
  26,169,Lord! Deliver me safely and my family from whatever they do
  26,170,So We delivered him safely and his family all together
  26,171,Except an old woman among the laggards
  26,172,Thereafter We destroyed the others
  26,173,"And We rained on them a rain, so odious is the rain of them that are warned"
  26,174,"Surely in that is indeed a sign, and in no way were most of them believers"
  26,175,"And surely your Lord, He is indeed The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Merciful"
  26,176,"The companions (i.e., inhabitants) of the Thicket cried lies to the Emissaries"
  26,177,"As Shuaayb said to them, \"Will you not be pious"
  26,178,Surely I am for you a trustworthy Messenger
  26,179,"So be pious to Allah, and obey me"
  26,180,And in no way do I ask of you any reward for (this); decidedly my reward (falls) upon no one except The Lord of the worlds
  26,181,"Fill up the measure, and do not be of them who make others losers"
  26,182,And weigh with the straight equitableness
  26,183,"And do not depreciate for mankind (the value) of their things, (i.e., their goods) and do not perpetrate (mischief) in the earth (as) corruptors"
  26,184,And be pious to Him Who created you and the earliest crowds
  26,185,"They said, \"Surely you are only one of the utterly bewitched"
  26,186,"And in no way are you (anything) except a mortal, like us, and decidedly we surmise that you are indeed one of the liars"
  26,187,"So let fall down on us lumps from the heaven, in case you are of the sincere"
  26,188,"He said, \"My Lord knows best whatever you do"
  26,189,Yet they cried him lies; then the torment of the Day of the Overshadowing took them (away); surely it was the torment of a Tremendous Day
  26,190,"Surely in that is indeed a sign, and in no way were most of them believers"
  26,191,"And surely your Lord, He is indeed The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Merciful"
  26,192,And surely it is indeed the (successive) sending down of The Lord of the worlds
  26,193,The trustworthy Spirit has come down with it
  26,194,"Upon your heart, that you may be one of the constant warners"
  26,195,"In an evident, Arabic tongue"
  26,196,"And surely it is indeed in the Scriptures (Literally: Zubur, i.e. the Psalms) of the earliest (people)"
  26,197,"And was it not a sign for them, that it is known to the men of knowledge of the Seeds (Or: sons) of ? Israel"
  26,198,And if We had been sending it down on some non-Arabs
  26,199,"Then he had read to them, in no way would they have been believers in it"
  26,200,Thus We have inserted it into the hearts of the criminals
  26,201,They (will) not believe in it until they see the painful torment
  26,202,"So that it will come up to them suddenly, and they are not aware"
  26,203,"Then they will say, \"will we be respited"
  26,204,"So, do they seek to hasten Our torment"
  26,205,"Then, have you seen, in case We give them enjoyment for (many) years"
  26,206,Thereafter (there) comes to them what they have been promised
  26,207,In no way will avail them whatever they had been given to enjoy
  26,208,And in no way did We cause (any) town to perish except that it had warners
  26,209,"For a Reminding, and in no way have We been unjust"
  26,210,"And in no way have Ash-Shayatin (The ever-Vicious (ones), i.e., the devils) been coming down with it"
  26,211,"And in no way does it behoove them, And in no way are they able to do (that)"
  26,212,Surely they are indeed kept apart from hearing
  26,213,"So do not invoke another god with Allah, then you should be of the tormented"
  26,214,"And warn your kinsmen, the nearest kin"
  26,215,And lower your wing to the ones who closely follow you of the believers
  26,216,"Yet, in case they disobey you, then say, \"Surely I am quit of whatever you do"
  26,217,"And put your trust in The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Merciful"
  26,218,Who sees you while you rise (in prayer)
  26,219,And (Ever) your turning about among the prostrate
  26,220,"Surely He, Ever He, is The Ever-Hearing, The Ever-Knowing"
  26,221,Shall I (fully) inform you on whom Ash-Shayatin keep coming down
  26,222,They keep coming down on every most vicious (and) constant falsifier
  26,223,"They are eager on hearing, and most of them are liars"
  26,224,"And the poets, the misguided closely follow them"
  26,225,Have you not seen that they wander in every valley
  26,226,And that they say what they do not perform
  26,227,"Excepting the ones who have believed, and done deeds of righteousness, and remember Allah much, and vindicate themselves ever after being unjustly treated. And soon the ones who did injustice will know by whatever overturning they will be overturned"
  27,1,"Ta Sin (These are the names of letters of the Arabic alphabet, and only Allah knows their meaning here).Those (Literally: that) are the ayat (Verses, signs) of the Qur'an and an Evident Book"
  27,2,A guidance and good tidings to the believers
  27,3,"Who keep up the prayer, and bring the Zakat, (i.e., pay the poor-dues) and they, (always) they, have certitude in the Hereafter"
  27,4,"Surely the ones who do not believe in the Hereafter, We have adorned for them their deeds, so they are blundering (blindly)"
  27,5,"Those are they for whom is an odious torment, and they, (always) they, are the ones who will be the greatest losers in the Hereafter"
  27,6,"And surely you indeed are granted (Literally: you are made to keep receiving) the Qur'an from very close to The Ever-Wise, The Ever-Knowing"
  27,7,"As Musa (Moses) said to his family, \"Surely I perceive a fire. Soon I will come up to you with news of it, or come up to you with a flaming brand that possibly you would warm yourselves"
  27,8,"So, as soon as he came to it, he was called out (that): \"Blessed are they who are in the fire, and they who are around it, and All Extolment be to Allah, The Lord of the worlds"
  27,9,"O Musa, surely I, Ever I, am Allah, The Ever-Mighty, The Ever-Wise"
  27,10,"And cast down your staff.\" So, as soon as he saw it shaking as if it were a jinni, he turned away withdrawing and did not retrace his steps. \"O Musa, do not fear (anything). Surely I (am The One); the Emissaries do not fear (anything) close to Me"
  27,11,"Except him who has done (an) injustice, (and) thereafter substituted fair (deeds) for odious (deeds). Then surely I am Ever-Forgiving, Ever-Merciful"
  27,12,"And put your hand into your bosom, (i.e., the bosom of your robe) it will come out (Literally: go out) white without any odious (imperfection) among nine signs to Firaawn (Pharaoh) and his people. Surely they have been an immoral people"
  27,13,"Then as soon as Our signs came to them, a beholding, (i.e., as a proof from Allah) they said, \"This is evident sorcery"
  27,14,"And they repudiated them, and their selves had (inner) certitude of them, out of injustice and exaltation. So look into how was the end of the corruptors"
  27,15,"And indeed We already brought Dawud (David) and Sulayman (Solomon) knowledge, and they (both) said, \"Praise be to Allah, Who has graced us over many of His believing bondmen"
  27,16,"And Sulayman was Dawud's heir, (Literally: inherited \"from\" Dawud \"David\") and he said, \"O you mankind, we have been taught the language (Literally: the manner of pronunciation) of (the) birds, and we have been brought (much) of everything; surely this is indeed the evident Grace"
  27,17,"And his hosts were mustered to Sulayman, of the jinn and humankind and birds. So they were duly dispensed"
  27,18,"Till, when they came up to the Valley of Ants, an ant said, \"O you ants, enter your dwellings so that Sulayman and his hosts would not definitely crush you, (while) they are not aware"
  27,19,"So he smiled broadly, laughing at its speech, and said, \"Lord! Dispense me to thank (You) for Your favor wherewith You have favored me and (both) my parents, and to do righteousness that satisfies You, and cause me to enter by Your mercy, among Your righteous bondmen"
  27,20,"And he reviewed the birds; then he said, \"what is it with me that I do not see the hoopoe? Or is he among the absent"
  27,21,"Indeed I will definitely torment him with a strict torment or indeed I will definitely slay him, or indeed he should definitely come up to me with an evident, all-binding authority"
  27,22,"Yet he stayed (a while) without being far away, then said, \"I have encompassed that which you have not encompassed, and I have come from Saba? to you with a tiding of certitude"
  27,23,"Surely I found a woman ruling over them, (Literally: a wife possessing them) and she has been brought (much) of everything, and she has a magnificent throne"
  27,24,"I found her and her people prostrating to the sun, apart from Allah; and Ash-Shaytan (The ever-vicious, i.e., the Devil) has adorned (i.e., made attractive) their deeds to them, so has barred them from the way, so that they are not guided"
  27,25,"So that they do not prostrate (themselves) to Allah, Who brings out what is hidden in the heavens and the earth. And He knows whatever you conceal and whatever you make public"
  27,26,"Allah, there is no god except He, The Lord of the Magnificent Throne.\" A prostration is to be performed here"
  27,27,"He said, \"We will soon look whether you have (spoken) sincerely or whether you are among the liars"
  27,28,"Go with this book (i.e., letter) of mine, then cast it to them; thereafter turn away from them, (and) so look what (answer) they return"
  27,29,"She said, \"O you chiefs, surely an honorable book has been cast to me"
  27,30,"Surely it is from Sulayman, (Solomon) and surely it is in The Name of Allah, The All-Merciful, The Ever-Merciful"
  27,31,"That \"You should not exalt yourselves against me, and come up to me as Muslims.\" (Or: in surrender)"
  27,32,"She said, \"O you chiefs, pronounce to me concerning my command; in no way have I affirmed (Literally: cutting) a command until you bear witness"
  27,33,"They said, \"We are endowed with power, and we are endowed with strict violence, (i.e., we are strong and able to fight) and the command (rests) with you; so look into what you command (us)"
  27,34,"She said, \"Surely, kings, when they enter a town, do corruption in it and make the mighty ones of its population humiliated. And thus they (too) will perform (similarly)"
  27,35,"And surely I am sending to them a present, so I am waiting to look into what the emissaries return with"
  27,36,"So, as soon as he (the envoy) came to Sulayman, (Solomon) he said, \"Would you supply me with wealth? Then what Allah has brought me is more charitable (i.e., better) than what He has brought you. No indeed, (but) you exult with your present"
  27,37,"Return to them. So indeed we will definitely come up against them with hosts they cannot withstand (Literally: of no withstanding). Indeed, we will definitely drive them out there from humiliated, and they will be (utterly) belittled"
  27,38,"He said, \"O you chiefs, whichever one of you will come up to me with (i.e., bring) her throne before they come up to me as Muslims?\" (Or: in surrender)"
  27,39,"A cIfrit (i.e., powerful, stalwart) of the jinn said, \"I will come up with it to you before you rise up from your station; and surely I am indeed powerful for it (and) trustworthy"
  27,40,"Said he in whose presence was knowledge of the Book, \"I will come up with it (i.e., bring) to you before your glance returns on you.\" (i.e., in the twinkling of an eye) Then, as soon as he saw it secured in position in his presence, he (Sulayman) said, \"This is of the Grace of my Lord that He may try me, whether I thank (Him) or be ungrateful. And whoever thanks (Him), then surely he thanks only for his (own) self, and whoever is ungrateful, (Or: whoever disbelieves) then surely my Lord is Ever-Affluent, (Literally: Ever-Wealthy, Ever-Rich) Ever-Honorable"
  27,41,"He said, \"Disguise her throne for her, that we may look into whether she is guided, or she is of the ones who are not guided"
  27,42,"So, as soon as she came, it was said, \"Is your throne just like this?\" She said, \" (It is) as though it were the (very) one.\" And (Sulayman) (Solomon) said, \"We were brought the knowledge before her, and we were Muslims.\" (i.e., we surrendered \"to Allah)"
  27,43,"And what she used to worship, apart from Allah, barred her (from belief); (for) surely she was of a disbelieving people"
  27,44,"It was said to her, \"Enter the tower.\" Then as soon as she saw it, she reckoned it a pool, and she uncovered both her shanks. He said, \"Surely it is a tower smoothed of crystal.\" She said, \"Lord! Surely I have done injustice to myself, and I (now) surrender (i.e., I am a Muslim) with Sulayman to Allah, The Lord of the worlds"
  27,45,"And indeed We already sent to Thamud their brother Salih, (saying), \"Worship Allah.\" Then, only then were they two groups, standing adversaries one with the other"
  27,46,"He said, \"O my people, why do you seek to hasten odious (deeds) before fair (ones)? Had you asked forgiveness from Allah, possibly you would be (offered) mercy"
  27,47,"They said, \"We augur ill of you and of (the ones) who are with you.\" He said, \"Your bird (of) augury is in the Providence of Allah. No indeed, (but) you are a people being tempted"
  27,48,And (there) was in the city nine (men of) a clan who corrupted in the land and did not act righteously
  27,49,"They said, \"Swear, one to another, by Allah that indeed we will definitely attack him and his family by night. Thereafter indeed we will definitely say to his patron, \"In no way did we testify to the perishing of his family; and surely we are indeed sincere (men)"
  27,50,"And they schemed a scheme, and We schemed a scheme, and they were not aware"
  27,51,"So look into how was the end of their scheming, (for) We destroyed them and their people all together"
  27,52,"So those are their houses, devastated because they did injustice; surely in that is a sign for a people who know (the Truth)"
  27,53,And We delivered the ones who believed and were pious
  27,54,"And Lut, (Lot) as he said to his people, \"Do you come up to (the) obscenity (while) you behold (its impurity)"
  27,55,"Do you (really) come up with lust to men rather than women? No indeed, you are a people who are ignorant"